        "committer": {
          "name": "Prakash Surya",
          "email": "surya1@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2011-10-05 15:25:32.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-723 Fix LC_EXT macros to be LDISKFS_DEVEL aware",
        "message": "LU-723 Fix LC_EXT macros to be LDISKFS_DEVEL aware\n\nAdded a new AC_DEFINE call to define the LDISKFS_DEVEL macro. A few\nLC_EXT* autoconf macros were also updated to use LDISKFS_DEVEL and 'do\nthe right thing' when building against the external ldiskfs devel\npackage. The specific autoconf macros that were updated are:\n\n * LC_EXT_INSERT_EXTENT_WITH_5ARGS\n * LC_EXT4_SINGLEDATA_TRANS_BLOCKS_SB\n * LC_EXT4_DISCARD_PREALLOCATIONS\n\nThese autoconf checks needed to be updated to use the ldiskfs headers\nand symbols when the LDISKFS_DEVEL directive is set. Otherwise the\nmacros would always check against the ext headers and symbols, which\ncauses problems if full kernel sources are not available.\n\nSigned-off-by: Prakash Surya <surya1@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: Icebbc794232d919ea0ef2e36bae40376ea5c14e9\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
